According to Albert Einstein, causality, meaning cause and effect,
cannot travel faster than the speed of light. This means that
information cannot travel faster than the speed of light. If a
transistor were to be constructed, say, 256 of them in my FPGA chip,
spread out in a 16 by 16 grid, and that transistor, with its output
ANDed with a clock wire, is the output of a quantum tunneling
transistor RNG. How it would work, is that the transistor gate is small
enough to tempt the electrons into flowing across every clock cycle
exactly 50% of the time. Because this is a form of quantum
teleportation of a electron, no information is being transferred, and
therefore, it is a 100% random bit generator.

The Quantum Tunneling Transistor RNG Idea Subproject is dedicated to
the Public Domain, however, once I add some code, that code will be
licensed under The VitaSet License, but the idea will remain dedicated
to the Public Domain.
